Great Pizza! I recommend the Classico Wood Fired Pizza. I live in the neighborhood, so I call ahead and it's usually ready in less than 20 mins. Definitely recommend calling in and ordering direct to support the business rather than having trouble with Uber Eats like it sounds some other reviewers have had. The folks who work here are genuinely nice and efficient and produce a great product! I'll happily order from here again and again!

We ordered the Meditarranea (Wood Fired Pizza Bianca) and have no regrets! As two people that are extremely picky about pizza, this was perfect! The crust had a nice char, while still being chewy. The veggies were fresh and Panino's didn't skimp!  Plus, our food was ready almost immediately when we ordered pickup via Grubhub, a rarity when compared to other places.  We'll definitely be getting pizza from here more often in the future.

Additionally, I love that they are a part of Visa Local Offers and I can get Uber credit for going here. There are two things I do wish they'd consider: 1. The thin-crust pizza is priced a bit steep at $4 a slice after tax. (at least, compared to $0.99 slices in NY) 2. The garlic knots taste good, but they are often dripping with butter/oil and the dough is a bit tough. A better dough & less butter would make these amazing.

Panino’s is awesome for a quick bite to eat at an affordable price. I often come here with my boyfriend and get slices to go. The staff is always friendly and there’s always options for different meats on the slices.  Aside from the slices, there’s pasta, garlic knots, and assortment of other options when just coming and going. The staff is always SUPER friendly as well. Love this place and definitely recommend.

Really cool little place in Lakeview. The pizza was really good, with the trademark char of a good Neapolitan pizza. We also shared a salad with arugal, fresh mozzarella and artichoke as well as a deep fried mozzarella appetizer. Everything came out fairly quickly, and our waitress was very helpful and friendly. We sat inside, but they do have some outdoor seating. Panino's also has a small bar with plenty of wine selections. I didn't see any beer options, but that definitely isn't a bad thing. The food here pairs much better with wine than beer anyway.

He told me he VOIDED my order and reimbursed me on my credit card, but I checked my statement the next day and he never voided it.  Short story - the owner is a thief and stole $25 from me.

We have been to Panino's Pizza several times over the years and have never been disappointed. The cozy, friendly atmosphere lends to the entire homestyle Italian culinary experience. Their appetizers are always on point, the bread is delicious and the entrees very flavorful. We recently tried their pizza as well and have been hooked ever since. Desserts are also a must, specifically the creamy rich Tiramisu and the Creme Brulee.

Nice small intimate spot for some good eats in Chicago. Had the fried calamari and it was excellent. Also ordered a pizza which was also very good. The meat was a little too much but that was just personal taste. Crust and sauce was right on point.

So glad I live walking distance from Panino's! The carry-out area always has hot slices of pizza to pick up and a case of delicous gelato :)  You cannot go wrong with any of their panini's- try the Modena- it's my fav.

I like their front and their back. Sounds creepy but I am just talking of the resturant and their pickup/delivery. Always quick and kind, I like the traditional Italian pizza and also the deep dish. I see their menu is huge and I should start to dig around it, but I like their pizza, too much
